Teams
Bing

Software Engineer 2
The Spartans team in the Bing Platform Group is looking for top tier software engineers. We are a team of elite engineers with experience in the Bing Stack.   We take on extremely high impact and valuable work and leverage our experience to quickly deliver it.   There is never a dull project in our portfolio, we are simply always working on the most strategic areas of Bing.   We are currently working on core improvements to the Bing platform and product and also on leveraging Bing technologies in modernizing enterprise applications.   We are heavily involved in the Next Generation Bing Application Platform and Next Generation Bing Features, Capacity and Efficiency Modeling and CRM/ERP Modernization.   
For some context, the key to Microsoft’s mission to “Empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more” is to build the best-in-class platforms and productivity services that are intelligent, personal and always accessible.   The Bing Platform team is right in the center of that vision.   The Bing Platform team is the brains behind Bing, BingAds and Cortana.   It builds and runs the platforms and the AI powering those offerings.   We also building the next generation platform and AI that will power many more of the productivity services and intelligent platforms envisioned across the company.   The Spartans engineers are the key catalysts and drivers in developing that platform and AI.   
Interested candidate *must have a CS degree* and should enjoy learning and ramping up on new technologies quickly.   While experience with the Bing stack would be beneficial, the team is willing to invest in ramping up stellar talent.
Required qualifications/experience:
• 5+ year experience working as a software engineer
• Strong programming skills in either C# or C++ or Java
• Strong software design skills
• Strong problem solving skills 
• Strong partnership, communication and coordination skills 
• Bachelor’s degree or equivalent in Computer Science or related field required

Additional qualifications/experience preferred:
• Experience with OOP, TDD and agile development models
• Experience with Microsoft Azure services is highly desirable
• Experience with SQL, NoSQL and BigData technologies
• Experience in implementing cross browser web applications 
• Experience building web services using ASP.NET (or similar technologies) and SDKs based on REST APIs, ODATA or JSON
• Knowledge of Windows, iOS/OSX, Android app development 
• Experience with Bing technology stack

